{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-sistent-component-js-content-file-path-src-collections-sistent-components-text-input-code-mdx","path":"/projects/sistent/components/text-input/code","result":{"data":{"mdx":{"body":"\nimport { Input, Box } from \"@sistent/sistent\";\n\nexport const codes = [\n  `<Input placeholder=\"Enter your name\" />`,\n  `<Input\n  label=\"Email Address\"\n  type=\"email\"\n  placeholder=\"example@domain.com\"\n  required\n/>`,\n  `<Input\n  placeholder=\"Share your thoughts...\"\n  multiline\n  rows={4}\n/>`,\n  `<Input color=\"primary\" placeholder=\"Primary\" />\n<Input color=\"secondary\" placeholder=\"Secondary\" />\n<Input color=\"success\" placeholder=\"Success\" />`,\n  `<Input\n  type=\"password\"\n  label=\"Password\"\n  placeholder=\"Enter password\"\n  required\n/>\n<Input\n  type=\"number\"\n  label=\"Age\"\n  placeholder=\"25\"\n/>\n<Input\n  type=\"tel\"\n  label=\"Phone\"\n  placeholder=\"+1 (555) 123-4567\"\n/>`,\n  `<Input\n  label=\"Username\"\n  placeholder=\"Enter username\"\n  error\n  helperText=\"Username is already taken\"\n/>`,\n  `<Input\n  label=\"Read-only Field\"\n  value=\"This field is disabled\"\n  disabled\n/>`\n];\n\n\n<p>\n  The <code>Input</code> component is essential for collecting user data in forms.\n  It provides immediate feedback during data entry, supports various input types,\n  and maintains consistency with your application's design system.\n</p>\n\n<a id=\"Basic Input\">\n  <h2>Basic Text Input</h2>\n</a>\n<p>\n  A simple input field for collecting single-line text data. This is the most common\n  form of text input used across applications.\n</p>\n<div className=\"showcase\">\n  <div className=\"items\">\n    <ThemeWrapper>\n      <Input placeholder=\"Enter your name\" />\n    </ThemeWrapper>\n  </div>\n  <CodeBlock name=\"input-basic\" collapsible code={codes[0]} />\n</div>\n\n<a id=\"Input with Label\">\n  <h2>Labeled Input</h2>\n</a>\n<p>\n  Inputs with labels provide better accessibility and user guidance. Labels clearly\n  identify the purpose of each input field and support screen readers.\n</p>\n<div className=\"showcase\">\n  <div className=\"items\">\n    <ThemeWrapper>\n      <Input\n        label=\"Email Address\"\n        type=\"email\"\n        placeholder=\"example@domain.com\"\n        required\n      />\n    </ThemeWrapper>\n  </div>\n  <CodeBlock name=\"input-labeled\" collapsible code={codes[1]} />\n</div>\n\n<a id=\"Multiline Input\">\n  <h2>Multiline Text Input</h2>\n</a>\n<p>\n  For longer text content that may span multiple lines. The multiline input\n  automatically expands to accommodate content and provides users with adequate space.\n</p>\n<div className=\"showcase\">\n  <div className=\"items\">\n    <ThemeWrapper>\n      <Input\n        placeholder=\"Share your thoughts...\"\n        multiline\n        rows={4}\n      />\n    </ThemeWrapper>\n  </div>\n  <CodeBlock name=\"input-multiline\" collapsible code={codes[2]} />\n</div>\n\n<a id=\"Color Options\">\n  <h2>Color Options</h2>\n</a>\n<p>\n  Input components support various color themes to match your application's\n  design system. Colors can convey different meanings or states within your interface.\n</p>\n<div className=\"showcase\">\n  <div className=\"items\">\n    <ThemeWrapper>\n      <Box sx={{ display: \"flex\", flexDirection: \"column\", gap: \"16px\", alignItems: \"flex-start\" }}>\n        <Input color=\"primary\" placeholder=\"Primary\" />\n        <Input color=\"secondary\" placeholder=\"Secondary\" />\n        <Input color=\"success\" placeholder=\"Success\" />\n      </Box>\n    </ThemeWrapper>\n  </div>\n  <CodeBlock name=\"input-colors\" collapsible code={codes[3]} />\n</div>\n\n<a id=\"Input Types\">\n  <h2>Different Input Types</h2>\n</a>\n<p>\n  Various input types provide specialized behavior and validation for different\n  data formats. Choose the appropriate type to enhance user experience and data quality.\n</p>\n<div className=\"showcase\">\n  <div className=\"items\">\n    <ThemeWrapper>\n      <Box sx={{ display: \"flex\", flexDirection: \"column\", gap: \"16px\", alignItems: \"flex-start\" }}>\n        <Input\n          type=\"password\"\n          label=\"Password\"\n          placeholder=\"Enter password\"\n          required\n        />\n        <Input\n          type=\"number\"\n          label=\"Age\"\n          placeholder=\"25\"\n        />\n        <Input\n          type=\"tel\"\n          label=\"Phone\"\n          placeholder=\"+1 (555) 123-4567\"\n        />\n      </Box>\n    </ThemeWrapper>\n  </div>\n  <CodeBlock name=\"input-types\" collapsible code={codes[4]} />\n</div>\n\n<a id=\"Error State\">\n  <h2>Error State</h2>\n</a>\n<p>\n  Error states provide visual feedback when validation fails. Combined with helper text,\n  they guide users toward resolving input issues effectively.\n</p>\n<div className=\"showcase\">\n  <div className=\"items\">\n    <ThemeWrapper>\n      <Input\n        label=\"Username\"\n        placeholder=\"Enter username\"\n        error\n        helperText=\"Username is already taken\"\n      />\n    </ThemeWrapper>\n  </div>\n  <CodeBlock name=\"input-error\" collapsible code={codes[5]} />\n</div>\n\n<a id=\"Disabled State\">\n  <h2>Disabled State</h2>\n</a>\n<p>\n  Disabled inputs are non-interactive and typically used for read-only data\n  or when certain conditions haven't been met to enable the input.\n</p>\n<div className=\"showcase\">\n  <div className=\"items\">\n    <ThemeWrapper>\n      <Input\n        label=\"Read-only Field\"\n        value=\"This field is disabled\"\n        disabled\n      />\n    </ThemeWrapper>\n  </div>\n  <CodeBlock name=\"input-disabled\" collapsible code={codes[6]} />\n</div>\n","frontmatter":{"title":"Text Input Code","description":"Code examples for implementing the Text Input component."}}},"pageContext":{"slug":"/projects/sistent/components/text-input/code","componentName":"text-input","availablePages":["code","guidance","overview"],"frontmatter":{"title":"Text Input Code","component":"text-input","description":"Code examples for implementing the Text Input component."}}},"staticQueryHashes":["4152005505","934084603"],"slicesMap":{}}